# Trivy ignore file — list CVE IDs or paths to suppress from the blocking gate.
# Format: one entry per line. CVE IDs (e.g. CVE-2023-12345) suppress that finding
# across all images; path patterns suppress findings in specific layers.
# Entries here are still reported in the SARIF Security-tab upload.
# Document WHY each entry is accepted before adding it.

# pyasn1 0.4.8 ReDoS (transitive via python-jose 3.4.0 -> rsa). The fix (pyasn1
# 0.6.3) is uninstallable: python-jose 3.4.0 hard-pins pyasn1<0.5.0. Not
# reachable in practice — pyasn1 only parses our trusted, configured JWT keys,
# never attacker-controlled input. Already accepted in pip-audit (ci.yml). Drop
# this when we migrate off python-jose. Tracked alongside #531.
CVE-2026-30922
